* When building websites, it is best to split up into many pieces of components, so we can work on a small piece of the website at a time.

* Components = a piece of the website designed to be reusable.
  - Component name starts with a capital letter.

  - Created in React using functions.

  - Example: textbox, button, chat messages.

  - Component Syntac
    - EX: <ChatInput></ChatInput>

    - EX(using self-closing syntax): <ChatInput />
      - Equivalent to: {ChatInput()}

* With React, we can create our own HTML elements and use our own elements to build the website.

* Fragments = similar to divs, they group elements together without creating an extra div. NOT a block element.
  - EX: <> </>

* Use component "App" to create a website.
